cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze financial commentaries from newspaper websites to identify stock market bubbles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques to identify patterns in the data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with financial data and market movements, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
